property.name: text
property.value: Sensors placed in a parking lot can be used to collect data (including which parking spot is taken, how long a car has parked on a spot). The parking lot can process the collected data and provide some services to clients to guide their parking. This demo illustrates these ideas. The dots are sensors on the parking spots. We use green color to indicate the spot is free and red to indicate the spot is taken. When a sensor detect a car arrives/leaves the spot, it sends an update to the server of the parking lot, which collects and processes sensor updates to provide information to parking clients. The "car model" component models when a car arrive/leave, and where if pick to park based on the information the server provides. It is a abstraction for all the cars dynamics during a specific of time. The components in the up right corner represents the server function, which receives sensor data and provides information the clients. The "singal light" component indicate whether the parking lot is full (using red color) or not (using green color).
